        },
        {
          "username": "Kerry Lawless",
          "rating": 1,
          "contributor_id": "112069311645644366022",
          "user_review_count": 37,
          "user_photo_count": 5,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVSRtNWKLdtMsqvuFziar0N4iC2t4au1YRUFazZQW-uOyk4KKcY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "This post isn\u2019t a reflection of the quality of care provided by the providers, but rather a reflection of their clerical staff and operations. I signed my daughter up and called One Medical to book a first-time appointment (she just needed height/weight and vaccinations updated). I told the person helping me this, and he booked us an appointment with a provider. He told me the email confirmation would come through as an urgent-care visit and that I shouldn\u2019t worry.\n\nOn the morning of the appointment (9 a.m.), I got a voicemail at 8:20 a.m. saying the appointment wasn\u2019t with a PCP and some other mumbled information that didn\u2019t make sense. It made me think the appointment was cancelled. So I called in to see what they meant. The woman I spoke with contacted the office (she wasn\u2019t even in the office), and they told her the appointment wasn\u2019t cancelled and that we should come in. So we went.\n\nWe arrive and are told that the provider won\u2019t be able to help us because she is urgent care. I see the provider anyway because I\u2019m so confused as to what is happening\u2014why make us come in if it should have been cancelled? The provider confirms she can\u2019t help us.\n\nIt was probably the most discombobulated experience I\u2019ve had with any provider\u2019s office, let alone a place that charges a membership fee to offer \u201cbetter\u201d care. I belonged to One Medical in the past and I loved their service, which is why we signed back up. I recommended it to numerous friends. I would no longer recommend it to anyone. Find a good MDs office that doesn\u2019t charge a membership fee. You\u2019ll get just as good of care if not better due to better operations as their office staff and operation staff do not seem to care or know what they are doing.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJYVU3UC0tbXZyOGJ3EAE!2m1!1s0x0:0x3050bf161bd382cb!3m1!1s2@1:CIHM0ogKEIaU7P--mvr8bw%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "a year ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2025-05-26T13:48:47+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "David Grier",
          "rating": 5,
          "contributor_id": "112209118707971894956",
          "user_review_count": 22,
          "user_photo_count": 4,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXc_HwUkohEO0NyXDQRB0vCVDpYJU6l9MCB_4BfJjlCfNo-MZpi=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "I dropped in at the Chelsea office for a couple of vaccinations. The staff were welcoming, and the facility felt more like a comfy living room than a medical office. I waited no more than five minutes before I was called back for my shots. The nurse was friendly and professional, explained clearly what I could expect, gave me my vaccinations and sent me on my way. This was my first experience at a One Medical office, and I am genuinely impressed.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2pONVlXaE1YekozV0VkRGR6RlVVM0EzTFVSb2JtYxAB!2m1!1s0x0:0x3050bf161bd382cb!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOjN5YWhMXzJ3WEdDdzFUU3A3LURobmc%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "9 months ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2025-09-15T17:43:38+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "Aaron",
          "rating": 1,
          "contributor_id": "103084632733149909853",
          "user_review_count": 18,
          "user_photo_count": 3,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUAvYHlhUkx5pw610IrROkrktziblbnjwRv-nGeUIcm4buDyLjV_w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "I tried calling ahead to confirm that the labs were open, but there was no way to reach anyone at the office directly. The person I did reach assured me the labs were open. Surprise, surprise, when I arrived, a very curt front desk staffer told me the labs were actually closed.\n\nI asked if he could contact another One Medical office to check whether their labs were open, and he flatly refused. So I walked 20 minutes to the next closest office, only to find their labs closed too.\n\nDon\u2019t go to a doctor you can\u2019t call. One Medical has gone downhill fast since Amazon acquired them. There\u2019s no care left, just business.",
